captions.text: - Well hello everyone.
My name is Tyler Oakley and I love fall,

or autumn, or whatever
you want to call it.

I don't know why I
became a robot about it,
but I'm living with it.
It's fine.
I love fall for a multitude of reasons.

I love the leaves crunching
underneath your feet.
I love burning the roof of my mouth
with a pumpkin spice latte.

I love layering and being
able to wrap around a flannel,
but then take it off, and put it on
when it gets a little bit chilly at night.

But I would have to say
the number one thing

that I love about this
time of year is Halloween.
Halloween is like Christmas for the gays.

At least for me, because
I love to don a costume.

Last year I showed you
my Halloween costume.
I was Perrie Edwards.
This is the look that I sported.
I was adorable and I don't know why
Zayn didn't call off the wedding

and get married to me instead,
but he didn't, so whatever.

But the best part is I
get to wear a new costume.
I feel adorable.
I feel adventurous.
And I feel like I'm having a good time

because this year I am Finn the
human from "Adventure Time".

He is the main character
on a Cartoon Network show
and I absolutely love the show
because it's fun, it's funny,
it's for kids, but it's also for adults,
and it handles social issues,

and it's just very positive
and smart and intelligent
and gets the job done.
I especially love this costume
because I get to have this cute hat.
I get to have this cute book bag

in case I wanna carry
all my alcohol in it.
I get to have a sword in case any bitches
try to come for me.
And I get to wear sexy short shorts
so I can show off my big ass thighs.

So I would say life is
good as Finn the human,

but I wanna know what are you
guys being this Halloween.
Let me know in the comments below
and send me pictures on Twitter.
And I wanna see all of your costumes.

I hope that you guys have
a fabulous Halloween.
Please be safe.
Please have fun.
Don't take advantage of people
that are wearing revealing outfits.
That's their choice.

It does not give you
permission to touch them.
And the most important thing,
fall only comes once a year.
Utilize the appropriate emojis,
whether it's the pumpkin, or the ghost,

or the leaves, or the acorn,
or the magic eight ball
because it's kind of relevant
when you're a witch this Halloween season.
I love you.
Have a good life.
I will see you guys next time.
And yeah, later.
Honestly, I am loving my costume
and I'm not at all sorry about it.
